== Events == * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1691|de|1691|ja|1691|zh|1691|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1691|qq=}} [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|de|Tokugawa-Shogunat|ja|徳川幕府|zh|德川幕府|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=}} granted permission to the wealthy merchant {{ill|Sumitomo family|de|Sumitomo-Familie|ja|住友家|zh|住友家|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sumitomo family|qq=}} to mine the [[:en:Besshi copper mine|Besshi Copper Mine]]. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1862|de|1862|ja|1862|zh|1862|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1862|qq=}} [[:en:June 6|June 6]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate's envoy to Europe, [[:en:Takenouchi Yasunori|Takeuchi Hoto]], signed the {{ill|London Memorandum|de|London-Memorandum|ja|ロンドン覚書|zh|伦敦备忘录|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/London Memorandum|qq=}} with British Foreign Secretary Russell, and agreed to open the markets of [[:en:Edo|Edo]] and {{ill|Osaka|de|Osaka|ja|大阪|zh|大阪|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka|qq=}}. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1871|de|1871|ja|1871|zh|1871|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1871|qq=}} [[:en:June 26|June 26]]) – [[:en:Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|Tokyo Prefecture]] announced the establishment of a road classification with a central carriageway and pedestrian sidewalks on both sides.
== Births == * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1867|de|1867|ja|1867|zh|1867|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1867|qq=}} [[:en:June 11|June 11]]) – [[:en:Inō Kanori|Ino Yoshinori]], an anthropologist and folklorist (died {{ill|1925|de|1925|ja|1925|zh|1925|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1925|qq=}}). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1870|de|1870|ja|1870|zh|1870|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1870|qq=}} [[:en:June 7|June 7]]) – {{ill|Ishikage Masaomi|de|Ishikage Masaomi|ja|石光真臣|zh|石光真臣|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishikage Masaomi|qq=}}, [[:en:Military personnel|Military Personnel]] (died {{ill|1937|de|1937|ja|1937|zh|1937|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1937|qq=}}).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kannin|Kannin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1017|de|1017|ja|1017|zh|1017|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1017|qq=}} [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – [[:en:Emperor Sanjō|Emperor Sanjō]], the 67th [[:en:Emperor of Japan|Emperor of Japan]] (died {{ill|976|de|976|ja|976|zh|976|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/976|qq=}}). * [[:en:Shōryaku|Shōkyō]] 2nd year / [[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1333|de|1333|ja|1333|zh|1333|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1333|qq=}} [[:en:June 21|June 21]]) – {{ill|Hōjō Chūji|de|Hōjō Chūji|ja|北条仲時|zh|北条仲時|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōjō Chūji|qq=}}, {{ill|Busho (Rank)|de|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|zh|武将|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=}} ・[[:en:Kamakura shogunate|Kamakura shogunate]] [[:en:Rokuhara Tandai|Rokuhara Tandai]] (died {{ill|1306|de|1306|ja|1306|zh|1306|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1306|qq=}}).
