{{Not to be confused with|May 9|qq=May 9}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月初九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 9일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 9''' is the 9th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1691|1691]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|de|Tokugawa-Shogunat|ja|徳川幕府|zh|德川幕府|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江戸幕府}} granted permission to the wealthy merchant {{ill|Sumitomo family|de|Sumitomo-Familie|ja|住友家|zh|住友家|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sumitomo family|qq=}} to mine the [[:en:Besshi copper mine|Besshi Copper Mine]]. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1862|1862]] [[:en:June 6|June 6]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate's envoy to Europe, [[:en:Takenouchi Yasunori|Takeuchi Hoto]], signed the {{ill|London Memorandum|de|London-Memorandum|ja|ロンドン覚書|zh|伦敦备忘录|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/London Memorandum|qq=}} with British Foreign Secretary Russell, and agreed to open the markets of [[:en:Edo|Edo]] and [[:en:Osaka|Osaka]]. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1871|1871]] [[:en:June 26|June 26]]) – [[:en:Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|Tokyo Prefecture]] announced the establishment of a road classification with a central carriageway and pedestrian sidewalks on both sides.
== Births == * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1867|1867]] [[:en:June 11|June 11]]) – [[:en:Inō Kanori|Ino Yoshinori]], an anthropologist and folklorist (died [[:en:1925|1925]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1870|1870]] [[:en:June 7|June 7]]) – {{ill|Ishikage Masaomi|de|Ishikage Masaomi|ja|石光真臣|zh|石光真臣|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishikage Masaomi|qq=}}, [[:en:Military personnel|Military Personnel]] (died [[:en:1937|1937]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kannin|Kannin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1017|1017]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – [[:en:Emperor Sanjō|Emperor Sanjō]], the 67th [[:en:Emperor of Japan|Emperor of Japan]] (died [[:en:976|976]]). * [[:en:Shōryaku|Shōkyō]] 2nd year / [[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:June 21|June 21]]) – {{ill|Hōjō Chūji|de|Hōjō Chūji|ja|北条仲時|zh|北条仲時|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōjō Chūji|qq=}}, {{ill|Busho (Rank)|de|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|zh|武将|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=}} ・[[:en:Kamakura shogunate|Kamakura shogunate]] [[:en:Rokuhara Tandai|Rokuhara Tandai]] (died [[:en:1306|1306]]).
