'''May 9''' is the 9th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshū|qid=Q96759839|1=senshū}}{{efn|ja|先勝|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Genroku|en|Genroku|qid=Q1325001|lt=Genroku|1=Genroku}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1691|en|1691|qid=Q7682|lt=1691|1=1691}} {{ill|June 5|en|June 5|qid=Q2622|lt=June 5|1=June 5}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|1=Tokugawa shogunate|2=ja|3=江戸幕府|de|Tokugawa-Shogunat|ja|徳川幕府|zh|德川幕府|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江戸幕府}} granted permission to the wealthy merchant {{ill|Sumitomo family|de|Sumitomo-Familie|ja|住友家|zh|住友家|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sumitomo family|1=Sumitomo family|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11381758}} to mine the {{ill|Besshi copper mine|en|Besshi copper mine|qid=Q994193|lt=Besshi Copper Mine|1=Besshi copper mine}}.
* {{ill|Bunkyū|en|Bunkyū|qid=Q730266|lt=Bunkyū|1=Bunkyū}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1862|en|1862|qid=Q7698|lt=1862|1=1862}} {{ill|June 6|en|June 6|qid=Q2620|lt=June 6|1=June 6}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate's envoy to Europe, {{ill|Takenouchi Yasunori|en|Takenouchi Yasunori|qid=Q6526546|lt=Takeuchi Hoto|1=Takenouchi Yasunori}}, signed the {{ill|London Memorandum|de|London-Memorandum|ja|ロンドン覚書|zh|伦敦备忘录|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/London Memorandum|1=Q11350850|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11350850}} with British Foreign Secretary Russell, and agreed to open the markets of {{ill|Edo|en|Edo|qid=Q215646|lt=Edo|1=Edo}} and {{ill|Osaka|en|Osaka|qid=Q35765|lt=Osaka|1=Osaka}}.
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1871|en|1871|qid=Q7746|lt=1871|1=1871}} {{ill|June 26|en|June 26|qid=Q2661|lt=June 26|1=June 26}}) – {{ill|Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|en|Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|qid=Q1189121|lt=Tokyo Prefecture|1=Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)}} announced the establishment of a road classification with a central carriageway and pedestrian sidewalks on both sides.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Keiō|en|Keiō|qid=Q776775|lt=Keiō|1=Keiō}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1867|en|1867|qid=Q7715|lt=1867|1=1867}} {{ill|June 11|en|June 11|qid=Q2617|lt=June 11|1=June 11}}) – {{ill|Inō Kanori|en|Inō Kanori|qid=Q713093|lt=Ino Yoshinori|1=Inō Kanori}}, an anthropologist and folklorist (died {{ill|1925|en|1925|qid=Q18107|lt=1925|1=1925}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1870|en|1870|qid=Q7741|lt=1870|1=1870}} {{ill|June 7|en|June 7|qid=Q2616|lt=June 7|1=June 7}}) – {{ill|Ishikage Masaomi|de|Ishikage Masaomi|ja|石光真臣|zh|石光真臣|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishikage Masaomi|1=Maomi Ishimitsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11585178}}, {{ill|Military personnel|en|Military personnel|qid=Q47064|lt=Military Personnel|1=Military personnel}} (died {{ill|1937|en|1937|qid=Q18647|lt=1937|1=1937}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Kannin|en|Kannin|qid=Q1193951|lt=Kannin|1=Kannin}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1017|en|1017|qid=Q19249|lt=1017|1=1017}} {{ill|June 5|en|June 5|qid=Q2622|lt=June 5|1=June 5}}) – {{ill|Emperor Sanjō|en|Emperor Sanjō|qid=Q357231|lt=Emperor Sanjō|1=Emperor Sanjō}}, the 67th {{ill|Emperor of Japan|en|Emperor of Japan|qid=Q208233|lt=Emperor of Japan|1=Emperor of Japan}} (died {{ill|976|en|976|qid=Q23782|lt=976|1=976}}).
* {{ill|Shōryaku|en|Shōryaku|qid=Q1324858|lt=Shōkyō|1=Shōryaku}} 2nd year / {{ill|Genkō (1331–1334)|en|Genkō (1331–1334)|qid=Q1194556|lt=Genkō|1=Genkō (1331–1334)}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1333|en|1333|qid=Q6004|lt=1333|1=1333}} {{ill|June 21|en|June 21|qid=Q2671|lt=June 21|1=June 21}}) – {{ill|Hōjō Chūji|de|Hōjō Chūji|ja|北条仲時|zh|北条仲時|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōjō Chūji|1=Hōjō Nakatoki|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q2054736}}, {{ill|Busho (Rank)|de|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|zh|武将|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|1=military commander|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11545923}} ・{{ill|Kamakura shogunate|en|Kamakura shogunate|qid=Q736839|lt=Kamakura shogunate|1=Kamakura shogunate}} {{ill|Rokuhara Tandai|en|Rokuhara Tandai|qid=Q938069|lt=Rokuhara Tandai|1=Rokuhara Tandai}} (died {{ill|1306|en|1306|qid=Q5716|lt=1306|1=1306}}).

